179874.name: Annual CO2 emissions per unit energy (kg per kilowatt-hour)
179874.description: Annual production-based emissions of carbon dioxide (CO2), measured in kilograms per kilowatt-hour of primary energy consumption. Production-based emissions are based on territorial emissions, which do not account for emissions embedded in traded goods.

source.additionalInfo:
The Global Carbon Budget dataset is available at https://doi.org/10.18160/gcp-2021 and https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5569235.

Full references:

Global Carbon Project. (2021). Supplemental data of Global Carbon Project 2021 (1.0) [Data set]. Global Carbon Project. https://doi.org/10.18160/gcp-2021.

Andrew, Robbie M., & Peters, Glen P. (2021). The Global Carbon Project's fossil CO2 emissions dataset [Data set]. Zenodo. https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5569235.

Our World in Data have renamed the category "bunker fuels" as "International transport" for improved clarity, which includes emissions from international aviation and shipping.

Primary energy consumption figures are sourced from BP and Shift Energy Data Portal. Link: https://www.bp.com/en/global/corporate/energy-economics/statistical-review-of-world-energy, https://www.theshiftdataportal.org/energy
